(223, 1, '2013-07-09 09:25:11', '2013-07-09 09:25:11', 'About Security Sense\nSecuritysense is a virtual knowledge center. Firoz Haider Khan (fhkhan@securitysense.org ) is the founder and chief security expert of securitysene.org, an IT/Information security consultant, a former head of Information Security Grameenphone (Telenor), Security Analyst, Bell Canada, Manager, Toshiba Information system, Singapore.\n\nThought is to share hands-on experience and help the community of professional and business management. Security sense is the most trusted and by far the largest source for information security ;Strategy and planning, IT / Technology Governance ,Risk Management, Telecom security, Security framework and architecture, Incident management, and security technology in the world.\nA range of individuals from auditors and network administrators, to chief information security officers will get solutions to the challenges they face.\nMany of the valuable Securitysense resources are free to all who ask. It also develops, maintains, and makes available at no cost, the largest collection of practical documents about various aspects of information security and Governance.\n\nChief Architect of Securitysense\n\nA distinguished leader of Information Technology Governance, IT service Management and IT security with expertise in diverse range of technologies within multiple industries settings. Demonstrated success managing IT, IT security, IT Strategy, IT Risk Management &amp; Assurance, IT Audit, Project management, IT Service Management. Well organized result oriented individual with proven ability to implement standard, procedures and processes that improve business functionality. Solid management skills, capable of leading and motivating individuals to maximize levels of productivity while forming cohesive team environments.\nFiroz Haider Khan (fhkhan@securitysense.org ) , is the founder and Chief Security expert of securitysene.org, an IT/Information security consultant, a former head of Information Security Grameenphone, Security Analyst Bell Canada.\n\nMr. Khan has consulted for several Fortune 500 companies in the Canada and Europe, Asia. including Bell Canada, Telenor, Robi Axiata and many more. Her competencies range from setting up risk management programs and developing enterprise network security architectures to constructing enterprise-wide security programs that connects computer security and business needs in a synergistic manner.\n\nMr. Khan has extensive knowledge and practical experience pertaining to legal and regulatory compliance. He has worked with the largest corporations within the Canada, Europe. to become compliant with OCC, SOX, GLBA, HIPAA, PCI and SAS70. Khan specializes in risk management, governance and the development of and implementation of security metrics.\n<h4>Mr. Khan’s area of Specialty area:</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>IT Service Management</li>\n	<li>IT / Information Security framework, architectures design</li>\n	<li>IT Governance, Strategy,</li>\n	<li>IT/ IT Security Project Management</li>\n	<li>Standard, policy, procedure development, implementation and management</li>\n	<li>ISO27001, COBIT, PCI DSS, ISO31000, ISO27005, more</li>\n	<li>IT Risk Management and Assurance</li>\n	<li>Service Level Agreements (SLA’s) &amp; operating level agreements (OLA’s)</li>\n	<li>Vulnerability assessment &amp; Penetration Test</li>\n	<li>Incident Management</li>\n	<li>Security Incident Management</li>\n	<li>BCM/DR Business Continuity Management</li>\n	<li>Process Management</li>\n	<li>Telecom security &amp; IT Audit</li>\n	<li>Budget Management</li>\n	<li>Resources Management</li>\n	<li>ISMS ISO 27001 Implementation &amp; Certification</li>\n	<li>COBIT 5, ITIL, eTOM</li>\n	<li>More than 15 Years’ Experience</li>\n	<li>IT Service Management</li>\n	<li>IT / Information Security framework, architectures design</li>\n	<li>IT Governance, Strategy,</li>\n	<li>IT/ IT Security Project Management</li>\n	<li>Standard, policy, procedure development, implementation and management</li>\n	<li>ISO27001, COBIT, PCI DSS, ISO31000, ISO27005, more</li>\n	<li>IT Risk Management and Assurance</li>\n</ul>', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-09 09:25:11', '2013-07-09 09:25:11', '', 222, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=223', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(363, 1, '2013-07-20 10:28:15', '2013-07-20 10:28:15', 'Securitysense is a virtual knowledge center. Firoz Haider Khan (fhkhan@securitysense.org ) is the founder and chief security expert of securitysene.org, an IT/Information security consultant, a former head of Information Security Grameenphone (Telenor), Security Analyst, Bell Canada, Manager, Toshiba Information system, Singapore.\r\n\r\nThought is to share hands-on experience and help the community of professional and business management. Security sense is the most trusted and by far the largest source for information security ;Strategy and planning, IT / Technology Governance ,Risk Management, Telecom security, Security framework and architecture, Incident management, and security technology in the world.\r\nA range of individuals from auditors and network administrators, to chief information security officers will get solutions to the challenges they face.\r\nMany of the valuable Securitysense resources are free to all who ask. It also develops, maintains, and makes available at no cost, the largest collection of practical documents about various aspects of information security and Governance.\r\n<h4>Chief Architect of Securitysense</h4>\r\nA distinguished leader of Information Technology Governance, IT service Management and IT security with expertise in diverse range of technologies within multiple industries settings. Demonstrated success managing IT, IT security, IT Strategy, IT Risk Management &amp; Assurance, IT Audit, Project management, IT Service Management. Well organized result oriented individual with proven ability to implement standard, procedures and processes that improve business functionality. Solid management skills, capable of leading and motivating individuals to maximize levels of productivity while forming cohesive team environments.\r\nFiroz Haider Khan (fhkhan@securitysense.org ) , is the founder and Chief Security expert of securitysene.org, an IT/Information security consultant, a former head of Information Security Grameenphone, Security Analyst Bell Canada.\r\n\r\nMr. Khan has consulted for several Fortune 500 companies in the Canada and Europe, Asia. including Bell Canada, Telenor, Robi Axiata and many more. Her competencies range from setting up risk management programs and developing enterprise network security architectures to constructing enterprise-wide security programs that connects computer security and business needs in a synergistic manner.\r\n\r\nMr. Khan has extensive knowledge and practical experience pertaining to legal and regulatory compliance. He has worked with the largest corporations within the Canada, Europe. to become compliant with OCC, SOX, GLBA, HIPAA, PCI and SAS70. Khan specializes in risk management, governance and the development of and implementation of security metrics.\r\n<h4>Mr. Khan’s area of Specialty area:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IT Service Management</li>\r\n	<li>IT / Information Security framework, architectures design</li>\r\n	<li>IT Governance, Strategy,</li>\r\n	<li>IT/ IT Security Project Management</li>\r\n	<li>Standard, policy, procedure development, implementation and management</li>\r\n	<li>ISO27001, COBIT, PCI DSS, ISO31000, ISO27005, more</li>\r\n	<li>IT Risk Management and Assurance</li>\r\n	<li>Service Level Agreements (SLA’s) &amp; operating level agreements (OLA’s)</li>\r\n	<li>Vulnerability assessment &amp; Penetration Test</li>\r\n	<li>Incident Management</li>\r\n	<li>Security Incident Management</li>\r\n	<li>BCM/DR Business Continuity Management</li>\r\n	<li>Process Management</li>\r\n	<li>Telecom security &amp; IT Audit</li>\r\n	<li>Budget Management</li>\r\n	<li>Resources Management</li>\r\n	<li>ISMS ISO 27001 Implementation &amp; Certification</li>\r\n	<li>COBIT 5, ITIL, eTOM</li>\r\n</ul>', 'About SecuritySense', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-20 10:28:15', '2013-07-20 10:28:15', '', 222, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=363', 0, 'revision', '', 0