(31, 6, 2, 'Question: 3', 1, 'Most B.C. government employees have received spam emails\r\nin their inbox. Of the more than 10 million emails that came to\r\nthe network in one week, what percentage would have been\r\nidentified as spam and blocked at the Internet Gateway.', 'Correct. It is\r\nnot surprising that some emails get through\r\nwhen the spammers are always getting better at\r\nmaking their emails look legitimate.', 'Sorry :( - The correct answer is B) 80% It is\r\nnot surprising that some emails get through\r\nwhen the spammers are always getting better at\r\nmaking their emails look legitimate.', 0, 0, '', 'single', 0, 0, 'a:4:{i:0;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:3:"95%";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:0;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}i:1;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:3:"80%";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:1;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}i:2;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:3:"65%";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:0;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}i:3;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:13:"Less than 65%";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:0;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}}', 0, 0, 0),
(32, 7, 1, 'Question: 2', 1, 'You can become a victim of identity theft after someone steals items containing personal information from your postal mailbox or recycling container at your home.', 'That''s Right! Thieves can find preapproved credit card offers in your mailbox or old unshredded bills in your recycling that contain enough information to commit fraud in your name. Shred documents with personal or financial information, follow-up on expected credits cards if late and perform self annual credit checks.', 'Sorry- The correct answer is True Thieves can find preapproved credit offers in your mailbox or old unshredded bills in your recycling that contain enough information to commit fraud in your name. Shred documents with personal or financial information, follow-up on expected credits cards if late and perform self annual credit checks.', 0, 0, '', 'single', 0, 0, 'a:2:{i:0;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:4:"True";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:1;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}i:1;O:27:"WpProQuiz_Model_AnswerTypes":7:{s:10:"\0*\0_answer";s:5:"False";s:8:"\0*\0_html";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_points";i:1;s:11:"\0*\0_correct";b:0;s:14:"\0*\0_sortString";s:0:"";s:18:"\0*\0_sortStringHtml";b:0;s:10:"\0*\0_mapper";N;}}', 0, 0, 0),
